definition: to be full to overflowing/to be brimming over with
to overflow/(literary) excessive/old variant of 鎰|镒[yi4]

sentences.english: The oil height is the highest point to which a tank can be filled without overflow.
sentences.chinese: 在油罐不满溢的条件下，能装油的最高位置称油高。

sentences.english: It is clearly water overflowing rain, the joy and fresh.
sentences.chinese: 那分明是流水满溢，雨后初晴的欣喜和清新。

sentences.english: Finally, love is in the air in Iceland.
sentences.chinese: 终于，冰岛的空气中满溢着爱情之气。

sentences.english: With the great black piano appassionato.
sentences.chinese: 和着硕大的漆黑钢琴的热情满溢。

sentences.english: My cup with blessings overflows, His oil anoints my head.
sentences.chinese: 祢用油膏了我的头，使我福杯满溢。

sentences.english: I really like every movie he directed.
sentences.chinese: 他的片子简直部部都是让我喜爱之情满溢。

sentences.english: The lake in its fulness seeks an outlet as a river.
sentences.chinese: 湖水在满溢的时候，会流成一条小河。

sentences.english: Cast abroad the rage of thy wrath: and behold every one that is proud, and abase him.
sentences.chinese: 要发出你满溢的怒气，见一切骄傲的人，使他降卑。

sentences.english: I first met my dear one, the joy of my heart;
sentences.chinese: 我初遇我的心爱，快乐满溢心房。

sentences.english: Silk trace moist, deep in quiet heart, with abundance and overflowing joy.
sentences.chinese: 丝丝清润，静静沁入心底，喜悦盈而满溢。

sentences.english: Swiss happiness, he writes, is "more than mere contentment, but less than full-on joy".
sentences.chinese: 在他笔下，瑞士人的幸福是“满足却不满溢”。

sentences.english: Water fills the lake from underground rivers stretching as far north as Ashenvale Forest.
sentences.chinese: 湖中满溢的是向北延伸至灰谷森林的地下河的水。

sentences.english: I didn’t know how to get overflowing information in my head on to paper.
sentences.chinese: 我不知道怎样把脑海中满溢的信息写出来。

sentences.english: My head Thou dost with oil anoint, and my cup overflows.
sentences.chinese: 祢用油膏了我的头，使我福杯满溢。

sentences.english: Single line captions are now more resistant to overflowing into two lines on minor changes.
sentences.chinese: 单行标题现在更耐分为两个小的改动就行满溢。

sentences.english: He filled the cup of my soul until it overflowed.

definition: (of a perfume or a foul odor) permeating the whole place/(of grease etc) dripping everywhere/flowing all over the place
to overflow/(literary) excessive/old variant of 鎰|镒[yi4]
to well up/to spill out (of water from a spring)
to pervade/to fill the air/diffuse/everywhere present/about to inundate (water)/permeated by (smoke)/filled with (dust)/to saturate (the air with fog, smoke etc)
variant of 彌漫|弥漫[mi2 man4]
to be full of (emotion)/to brim with (love, tears etc)
to gush/to squirt/to surge/to well out/to overflow
